Variables in R Basics:

# this is a comment - R is going to read as a comment anything starting with #

variable <- 100
Now 100 is assigned to variable

bank <- 1000
The ways to assign:
bank.account <- 100
bankAccount <- 100
bank_account <- 100
Where bank.account is the most popular.

Using ctrl L we can clean our console.

Easy way of using Variables:

deposit <- 20
bank.account <- bank.account + deposit
bank.account
The result is 120 now.
